ðŸ”¸ LEGB Rule in Python

| Level | Scope Type | Value of `x`                     |
| ----- | ---------- | -------------------------------- |
| L     | Local      | `"Local X"` inside `inner()`     |
| E     | Enclosing  | `"Enclosing X"` inside `outer()` |
| G     | Global     | `"Global X"` outside functions   |
| B     | Built-in   | `len()` is a built-in function   |


